<br>
It's hard to describe how much easier many encounters became.  I take on 2-3 mobs all the time now when soloing with near 0 risk.  Or for chaining pets, I stick malosini to make sure everthing sticks well, then I root, then blind, then take my merry time casting next pet leg buffing and making swords from gloves.  The Instill from earring lasts 96 seconds max and it's almost never resisted, less then my Malosini gets resisted by a longshot.  The 4 sec cast time makes it fast enough to root non-sow mobs as they run at me.  If a mob is snared and does not nuke/summon.  It's game over, I will win.<br>
<br>
I do aggro kite in PoN all the time with a snare caster.  They snare a mob on pull, I malo as he's coming.  Then I root the mob, aggro-kiter casts ensnare about 5 times to get WAY up on hate list, then he just kites the mob in circles around me while a /pet taunt off pet bashes him and I boot nuke or real nuke while medding on a horse.  Every once in awhile puller gets adds and I just root/malosini them and keep them rooted for the whole fight while we kill the main.<br>
<br>
Most mobs I have kept rooted while killing one with pet was 4.  After getting malo on all of them they all stick for the full 96 second pretty well, so it's easy to keep it on them all.  Higher MR on the mobs just makes them either resist root right off the bat, or it breaks faster.  Epic pet breaks root really fast with stuns and such.<br>
<br>
I have even soloed with just Boots of Bladecalling and root to see if it's possible.  I put on my extended range III item in Akheva, got to max casting range and nuked a Centi.  I stated clicking earring as soon as nuke went off, nuke is slightly larger range then root.  Mob gets rooted like 25 feet away from me.  Then I back out range again, and repeat until dead.  It takes awhile, but it's possible.  What I started doing later was doing this like 3 times in row to get high on hate list, then turn off pet taunt, break root and aggro kite.  Pet takes way less damage, I barely use any mana and kills stay fast.<br>
<br>
In duels, dude.  People are suprised to say the least, they don't expect that mage to root them.  I have stuck root on people with 180 MR before casting mala, not very often, but it has stuck.  I dueled a 60th Shadow Knight awhile ago, it was a great fight and we both ran ourselves low on Mana.  Finally I got him to lose track of me, so I malosini'd, rooted, blinded him, then chain cast pets and boot nuked until he died.  While refreshing blind and root every once in awhile.<br>
<br>
When I needed cash to try and finish epic awhile ago, I put the earring up for sale in Bazaar for 1 million plat, then I just could not handle it so I took it down 2 min later.  I knew if I sold It I would never root again. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
