<br>
Blind is VERY usefull if you know how to use it.  Here's a few scenarios...<br>
<br>
-If mob is near the person on top of the hate list and he gets blinded, he will just continue to hit that person.  <br>
<br>
-If a mob is Not within melee range of the person on top of the hate list, the mob will run in a &quot;fear type pattern&quot; looking for that person, even if other people are in melee range or pets are beating on it.<br>
<br>
-If a mob is blinded with nobody it hates in melee range, it will again run in the &quot;fear type pattern&quot;<br>
<br>
So yes, I fear-kite mobs with blind.  You should be able to see how now.  I pull with Firebolt of Tallon, root mob on the way in.  I then blind him, and nail him with a FoT again to break root and REALLY piss him off.  Send in pet and sit down to med after the 2nd FoT lands.  The mob will break root and just run off in the fear pattern looking for me while pet gets free hits.  Eventually, blind wears off then he comes back for me.  I stand up, blind on the way in, then sit down and med more while he runs off with pet still beating on him.<br>
<br>
Or if I'm getting beat on with no pet, blind the mob then back out of melee range and the mob will &quot;fear&quot; away while trying to find me.  Gives me time to cast a pet or gate etc.<br>
<br>
Or if I blind a mob on a raid, they seem to be more likely to stay on the main tank and not switch around to other people.  This can be bad though if somebody not in melee range top's off the hate list and the mob goes running to find them, use with caution. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
